A = (A - B) \cup (A\cap B)
P(A) = P(A - B) + P(A\cap B)
A \cup B = (A - B) \cup (A \cap B) \cup (B - A),
P(A\cup B) = P(A - B) + P(A\cap B) + P(B - A).
P(A\cup B) = P(A) + P(B - A).
P(A\cup B) = P(A) + P(B - A) + P(A\cap B) - P(A\cap B)  = P(A) + P(B) - P(A\cap B).
